HEADWORD: Braky
<hw>Brak"y</hw> <pr>(br⟦amac⟧k"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of
brakes; abounding with brambles, shrubs, or ferns; rough;
thorny.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the woods and <qex>braky</qex> glens.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>braless</ent>⟦br⟧
